The main attention is paid to the surgical patient. Students will be introduced with methods and risks of anaesthesia, including the managment of airways. They will be learned the principles and practical issues of postoperative care, including the indications and performance of infusion therapy. Students will learn resuscitation from cardiac arrest.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach the students the main principles for managment of anaesthesia, pre- and postoperative care  and to introduce the assessment of critically ill patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the student knowns the main methods and complications of anaesthesia; is able to give pre-anaesthesia recommendations to the patient; is able to secure the open airways; is able to provide CPR (basic life support+AED, in-hospital BLS); knows the indications and practical conductiong of fluid therapy; is able to give recommenrdations for psotoperative care to surgical patient; is able to recognize the patient in shock and knows the principles of management of shock.
